# Toolkit Conventions

This is a **distribution toolkit**, not an application. It ships Cursor rules, skills, agents, and commands that get installed into `~/.cursor/` for use in other projects. There is no build step, no runtime, and no dependencies. Content is Markdown, YAML templates, and one shell script (`install.sh`).

Do not add package managers, build scripts, test frameworks, or CI pipelines to this repo.

## Component Types

### Rules (`rules/*.mdc`)

`.mdc` files with YAML frontmatter. These are templates copied into demo projects by the scaffold skill; they are not applied to this repo.

```yaml
---
description: What the rule enforces
alwaysApply: true          # or false with a globs field
globs: "**/*.yml"           # optional, only when alwaysApply is false
---
```

### Skills (`skills/<name>/SKILL.md`)

A directory containing `SKILL.md` with YAML frontmatter and an optional `templates/` subdirectory for reference files.

```yaml
---
name: dd-<name>
description: One-line description used by Cursor to match the skill to user intent
---
```

### Agents (`agents/<name>.md`)

A single Markdown file with YAML frontmatter.

```yaml
---
name: dd-<name>
description: One-line description
model: inherit
readonly: true              # optional, omit if the agent needs write access
---
```

### Commands (`commands/<name>.md`)

A single Markdown file, **no frontmatter**. Keep under 20 lines. The body should briefly describe intent and delegate to a skill or agent.

## Naming

All artifacts use a `dd-` prefix.
